parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Sticking or Hard to Press
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking or hard-to-press brake pedal can lead to delayed or incomplete braking, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal does not travel to the floorboard
requires excessive force to press
feels hard or stiff
or has a spongy feel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Brake Motor Failure (Left Front Brakes)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic brake motor can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The left front brakes fail to engage
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
or there is a loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Carbon Monoxide Ingress into Passenger Compartment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ingress of carbon monoxide into the passenger compartment can cause serious health risks, including headaches, dizziness, nausea, and even death, especially when the heat is in use.
symptoms: Carbon monoxide odor or presence in the passenger compartment
especially when the heat is turned on
symptoms of carbon monoxide poisoning such as headaches
dizziness
and nausea.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
unusual engine noises
difficulty starting the engine
sudden loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering rack can cause the steering system to malfunction, making it difficult or impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering feels stiff or difficult to turn
the steering locks up or becomes stuck
excessive wear on the power steering rack
fluid leaks from the steering system
difficulty turning left or right.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle malfunction can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly accelerate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The throttle goes into open position after putting the vehicle in reverse
the throttle sticks in the 6:00 or 12:00 position
unexpected acceleration
loss of control.
